Description: Their mission is to make US manufacturing 15% more efficient.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Their mission is to make US manufacturing 15% more efficient. They do so by connecting manufacturing machines to simulation servers that enable real time analysis and correction of machining results. STEP Tools, Inc. has existed in three phases. In the first phase, from 1990 to 2000, they worked with a worldwide community of experts to develop protocols for sharing product model data between enterprises. In the second phase, from 2000 to 2015, they built upon their earlier experience to create a rich and powerful software stack for viewing and manipulating product models. Their software is used in millions of CAD, CAM, and BIM stations. Now in the third phase, they enable the sharing of measurable product models, in real time, on the digital thread, using smart phones and browsers. To participate, connect your manufacturing machines, including traditional machine tools, 3D printers and robots, to simulation servers known as digital twins. You will then be able to share correctable 3D models of what you are making between design, planning, manufacturing and inspection across the supply chain. The benefits are faster communication, instantaneous inspection and the ability to automate many new processes. With their technology, your manufacturing operations will become 15% more efficient by slowing down to reduce tool wear when there is flexibility, and speeding up to meet a deadline when the schedule is tight.

Description: Hunters Gate Holdings is a private holding company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Hunters Gate Holdings is a private holding company based in Atlanta and Charlotte.  They acquire and invest in lower middle-market companies in the Industrial, Energy & Power and Business Services sectors based in the Southeastern U.S. and Texas with EBIT of $1-10 million.  They seek profitable, well-run companies with a strong market position that are seeking a change in ownership or growth capital. As a private holding company, Hunters Gate provides a compelling alternative to strategic buyers and traditional private equity firms. They do not integrate companies into their operations, and they do not reduce headcount to generate synergies. They invest in companies for the long term and do not sell companies after a brief ownership period. As a result, they believe they are a responsible aquiror of businesses, preserving the legacy of strong companies and providing long-term stability for employees, customers and vendors. The principals of Hunters Gate have been investing in lower middle-market businesses for over 20 years and have helped companies in a variety of sectors reach new levels of success.

Growing up in rural Kentucky, RTF Founder Chris Sanders saw this problem first-hand, and decided to do something about it. The Rural Technology Fund (RTF) recognizes the very real “digital divide” between rural and non-rural areas. For rural communities to remain economically viable and appealing as a home to new industry, technology-based or not, these communities need to fully understand the potential that technology can provide, and encourage growth of those skills in local youth. Ensuring that students from rural areas are able to go out and acquire the education they need and desire will go a long way to helping these communities overcome the digital divide. Unfortunately, technology is unlike agriculture, healthcare, or even legal fields, where even the smallest communities have practitioners who can provide support within the community. In the ultimate Catch-22, because rural areas are generally not where technology companies have offices, students interested in this type of career often find little community support in terms of local internship opportunities, education training programs, and/or mentoring opportunities. The founder of the RTF and several of its board members encountered this scenario when they graduated from their own rural high schools. With this personal experience driving The Rural Technology Fund, we seek to lower barriers to rural students and ensure that they have an easier road to technology-based careers. This is supported by several different programs.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Education, Other, Social Impact
